07/08/2006
RUDARE, Kosovo, Serbia -- KFOR Commander Lieutenant General Giuseppe Valotto on Friday (4 August) said there would be no repetition of the March 2004 ethnic violence in Kosovo. 
During a meeting in Rudare, he assured the Deputy Chief of the Serbian Army, General Zdravko Ponos, that KFOR stands ready to respond to any unrest and protect Kosovo Serbs. 
Both described the level of co-ordination between KFOR and the Serbian Army as very good. 
(Glas javnosti, B92 - 05/08/06)
